The problem of finding edge-disjoint paths is a classic problem in graph theory and has been extensively studied in computer science. The length constraints add an additional layer of complexity to the problem. The use of random partition and structural results suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The problem also involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are covered by the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT) categories. Finally, the use of FPT algorithms and kernelization suggests that the paper may also belong to the Complexity Theory (cs.CC) category.
